Steps to Update HDL Program:

1. libero & Update HDL Code

2. Verify and Save HDL file and press the "Build Hierarchy" button in the Design Hierarchy window to refresh

3. Make new connections in CAPE, save

4. Right click and select “Generate Component” for all SmartDesigns with an “i” icon

5. Right-click on the CAPE and select “Export Component Description (TCL)” to gateware/sources/FPGA-design/script_support/components/CAPE/DEFAULT/

6. cp gateware/work/libero/hdl/*.v gateware/sources/FPGA-design/script_support/components/CAPE/DEFAULT/HDL/

7. Right-click on the HDL file in the Design Hierarchy and select Export Component Description to /gateware/sources/FPGA-design/script_support/components/CAPE/DEFAULT/blinky_config.tcl

8. close Libero

9. python3 build-bitstream.py ./build-options/default.yaml

10. Press "User" button (press and hold the USER button while connecting your Fire to the USB port on your machine) and copy over the ./bitsteam folder

11. Press "Reset" button, tio /dev/ttyACM1

12. sudo /usr/share/beagleboard/gateware/change-gateware.sh ./bitstream




